rows: The request has been completed sucessfully and the resource value is not equal to zero. In this case, the request body should contain the authentication status code. If it contains 0, the authentication is successful. In case of unsuccessful authentication, the authentication status code will equal 1 and the request body will contain a message about the cause of the unsuccessful authentication.
The server cannot provide access to the resource specified in the request (for example, if a method name is spelled incorrectly). Request body can contain additional information.
